Teamwork. Leadership. Management. Leadership styles. Motivation. Cooperation. Performance evaluation. Team relations.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to provide knowledge about the basic principles and management of the work of design teams to organize more effective teamwork in design projects. In addition, create opportunities to learn the basics of teamwork to enable students to understand and address important issues related to teamwork in organizations.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course the student will:  1) understand the nature and role of management in directing the activities of an organization; 2) know and distinguish between the sub-activities of management, i.e. the main functions (planning, organization, control, leadership, communication and decision-making) based on management as a whole; 3) be able to take into account the individual differences of people in occupational activities; 4) know the principles of teamwork processes and analysis;  5) be able to participate effectively in teamwork on the position of both leader and team member;
